  "metadata": {
    "what_it_measures": "Consumer Price Index for All Urban Consumers: All Items Less Food and Energy. BLS. Monthly, mid-month 8:30 ET. Core excludes volatile F&E.\n",
    "why_it_matters": "Hot CPI = rate fear = equity drawdown (esp. duration/multiple-sensitive names). Core CPI is the Fed's benchmark for underlying inflation; it determines the pace of rate hikes/cuts.\n",
    "scoring_rule": "Score as YoY % change vs 2% target: < 2.0% \u2192 +60 | 2.0-2.5% \u2192 +20 | 2.5-3.0% \u2192 -20 | 3.0-4.0% \u2192 -50 | > 4.0% \u2192 -80. Phase 3.\n"
  },
